The Test Cover problem is a well-known problem in computational complexity theory and has connections to various subfields of computer science. The problem involves finding a minimum set of tests that can separate all pairs of vertices in a given graph. This problem is closely related to graph theory, combinatorial optimization, and computational geometry. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
